    <note type="source">Brill's New Pauly: "Valens, Bishop of Mursa, 4th cent., Bishop of Mursa (modern Osijek, Croatia), spoke against Athanasius at the First Synod of Tyre in 335, and accompanied Constantine (Constantinus [1]) to Constantinople in early 336. With Ursacius of Singidunum (modern Belgrade), he was an important supporter of the Arian movement....." Letsch-Brunner, Silvia (Zürich), “Valens”, in: Brill’s New Pauly, Antiquity volumes edited by: Hubert Cancik and , Helmuth Schneider. Consulted online on 01 November 2016</note>
